<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2653> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2653" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Commanded the center at Callinicus (Liv. 42.58.13). See Legates." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2652> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2652" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Manlius L. f. is probably a son of L. Manlius Acidinus Fulvianus, Cos. 179. Münzer RE no. 43 considers M. f. suspect since the praenomen M. was forbidden at least in any patrician branch of the family, which, if the above identification is correct, is the only branch in question here. Furthermore, the adoption of a Fulvius into the family indicates that its numbers were greatly reduced. Münzer suggests that Manlius L. f. may be L. Manlius, Quaestor in 168." .
